# Add generated local-reduce aux-output store support for FlexGEMM.
#
# PyTorch/Inductor owns the reduction semantics and emits generated CuTeDSL
# TensorSSA or physical combine/finalize code. QuACK owns only the physical
# grouped store/reduction contract: grouped-N stores TensorSSA-reduced values,
# while grouped-M uses generated callbacks with lane-local physical reduction.

